topic.title: SCSI Enclosure Services (SES) Command

note.p: This feature will be available in Revision B RTP silicon

section.title: MRPC Command ID: 0x1E
section.p: This command sends the SES control or status message to firmware, and retrieves the status data from firmware.

row.entry: The handler thread is not idle

body.p: This field provides the following configuration options for the SES command.
This field provides the SES page code.
The data offset is used when splitting one complete SES message into several parts.
The data length of current message(in unit of byte).
The total data length for a complete SES command, typically equal to the total page size(in unit of byte).
The Data field is optional. Send Diagnostics command typically will have associated data, and the Receive Diagnostics command typically does not have associated data.

section.title: SEND DIAGNOSTICS
section.p: The Send Diagnostics command is used to send an SES control page to firmware.
This field should be 0 to perform a Send Diagnostics command.
This field provides the SES page code.
The data offset is used when splitting one complete SES message into several parts.
The data length of current message(in unit of byte).
The total data length for a complete SES command, typically equal to the total page size(in unit of byte).
The SES page data.

section.title: RECEIVE DIAGNOSTICS
section.p: The rReceive Diagnostics command is used to send an SES status page to firmware.
This field should be 1 to perform a Receive Diagnostics command.
This field provides the SES page code.
The data offset is used when splitting one complete SES message into several parts.
The data length of current message(in unit of byte).
The total data length for a complete SES command, typically equal to the total page size(in unit of byte).

section.title: Get Result
section.p: The Get Result command is used to get the result after a Send Diagnostics or Receive Diagnostics command.
This field should be 2 to perform a Get Result command.
This field provides the SES page code.
The data offset is used when the command results are split into several parts. The data offset should be continuous with previous command if the data is retrieved in several parts.
The data length that current command will retrieve(in unit of byte).
The total data length that should be retrieved by host(in unit of byte).
The command status.
The output data length.
The data offset from which the data is retrieved.
This field indicates generic information describing a reported condition.
This field indicates further information related to the condition reported in the SENSE KEY field.
This field indicates detailed information related to the condition reported in the ADDITIONAL SENSE CODE field.
The retrieved data.

ol.li:
Send Diagnostics for SES Enclosure Control page
Write address 0 with data: 0x00000200 0x00880088 0x88005502 0x00000000 0x20020080 0x00000080 0x00020080 0x00020000 0x00000000 0x20020000 0x00000000
Write address 2048 with data: 30

Receive Diagnostics for SES Configuration page
Write address 0 with data: 0x00000101 0x00020000
Write address 2048 with data: 30

Get Result for SES Configuration page
Write address 0 with data: 0x00000102 0x00580058
Write address 2048 with data: 30
Read address 1024 for 88 DWORD data

note.p: After the send diagnostics and receive diagnostics operation, Switchtec sends an asynchronous notification to the requester.
